      textEn: [
        "The northern landscape: a thousand li of ice sealed, ten thousand li of snow drifting. Gazing at the Great Wall, inside and out, only vast whiteness remains; up and down the great river, the surging torrent has suddenly ceased. Mountains dance like silver serpents, highlands gallop like wax elephants, all vying to match heaven in height. Wait for a clear day, and see the land dressed in red and white, extraordinarily enchanting.",
        "This land so rich in beauty has made countless heroes bow in homage. Pity that the First Emperor of Qin and Emperor Wu of Han were somewhat lacking in literary grace; the founders of Tang and Song fell slightly short in poetic flair. The pride of heaven for a generation, Genghis Khan, knew only how to bend his bow at great eagles. All are past and gone. For truly great figures, look to the present day."
      ],
