      textEn: [
        "I say you are April on earth;\nyour laughter lights up the four winds;\nlightly you dance and change in the glow of spring.",
        "You are the cloud and mist of early April skies,\nthe softness of wind at dusk,\nstars flashing unawares,\nfine rain sprinkled before the flowers.",
        "That lightness, that grace — you are;\nwearing the crown of a hundred vivid flowers,\nyou are innocence, you are solemnity,\nyou are the full moon every night.",
        "The goose-yellow after snow melts, you resemble;\nthe green of fresh new buds, you are;\ntender and joyful,\nthe water’s shimmer floats with the white lotus of your dreams.",
        "You are tree after tree in bloom,\nswallows murmuring between the beams —\nyou are love, you are warmth, you are hope,\nyou are April on earth!"
      ],
