      textEn: [
        "In the twelfth month of the fifth year of Chongzhen, I was staying at West Lake. After three days of heavy snow, all sounds of people and birds on the lake had ceased. That evening at the first watch, I took a small boat, wrapped in fur clothing with a brazier, and went alone to view snow at the Heart-of-the-Lake Pavilion. Frost and mist filled the air; sky, clouds, mountains, and water merged into whiteness above and below. The only shadows on the lake were a single trace of the Long Causeway, a dot of the pavilion, a mustard-seed of my boat, and two or three grains of people in the boat.",
        "Upon reaching the pavilion, two men had spread felt mats and sat facing each other, with a servant boy heating wine until it boiled. Seeing me, they were overjoyed: “Who would have thought there could be another such person on the lake!” They pulled me to join their drinking. I drained three large cups and took my leave. When I asked their names, they were from Nanjing, visiting here. As I got off the boat, the boatman murmured: “Don’t say the master is obsessed — there are those even more obsessed than the master.”"
      ],
